    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/credibility-assessment-team-depuy",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required gradation level. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is acknowledged; the single-condition test protocol is consistent with ASTM F1717 standard practice and the regulatory submission scope. The E/uval metric is satisfied for all three QoIs across both laboratory datasets. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support the claim that the FEA framework reliably predicts ASTM F1717 compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. Package accepted for regulatory submission.",
